org.pepstock.charba.client.data

Class StackedAreaDataset

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepstock.charba.client.commons.NativeObjectContainer
      • org.pepstock.charba.client.data.Dataset
        • org.pepstock.charba.client.data.LineDataset
          • org.pepstock.charba.client.data.StackedAreaDataset
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasDataPoints

    public class StackedAreaDataset
extends LineDataset
    The stacked area chart allows a number of properties to be specified for each dataset. These are used to set display properties for a specific dataset.
    Extends the line dataset setting stack property.
    Author:
    Andrea "Stock" Stocchero

      • setBorderJoinStyle

        public void setBorderJoinStyle(JoinStyle borderJoinStyle)
        Sets how two connecting segments (of lines, arcs or curves) with non-zero lengths in a shape are joined together (degenerate segments with zero lengths, whose specified end points and control points are exactly at the same position, are skipped).
        There are three possible values for this property: round, bevel and miter. By default this property is set to miter.
        Parameters:
        borderJoinStyle - There are three possible values for this property: round, bevel and miter.
